      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "security: add Security Matrix runtime-fact audit model",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a Security Matrix runtime-fact evaluator.\n- Models actor, influence source, tool capability, approval state, and operator policy as separate inputs.\n- Adds default policy data, a deterministic evaluator, tool capability resolution, an audit-event object builder, tests, and documentation.\n- Adds a before-tool-call fact adapter and anchors it to the trusted tool policy boundary through an inert audit-event builder.\n- Removes the unsupported `security.matrix.audit.enabled` placeholder so this PR does not reserve a parallel config surface.\n- Removes the Security Matrix production files from the dead-code allowlist after adding the trusted-policy boundary import path.\n- Hardens custom policy parsing so malformed decisions cannot weaken the default policy.\n\n## Scope\n\nThis PR remains non-enforcing and observe-only.\n\nIt does not block tool calls, require confirmation at runtime, emit runtime diagnostic events, change UI, change plugin behavior, or alter runtime tool execution. The before-tool-call adapter only builds an audit event object from explicit boundary facts. Runtime diagnostic emission, canonical config, CLI display, and enforcement remain future work.\n\n## Validation\n\nLatest cleanup head: `9086754a013ef957021e7bf551409ba853d4cb2a`.\n\nGitHub Actions have been triggered for the latest head.\n\nFocused commands to run against this head:\n\n```bash\npnpm test src/security/security-matrix/evaluate.test.ts\npnpm changed:lanes --base upstream/main --json\npnpm exec oxlint src/security/security-matrix/ src/plugins/trusted-tool-policy.ts\nnode scripts/format-docs.mjs --check docs/security/security-matrix.md\ngit diff --check upstream/main...HEAD\n```\n\nEarlier focused validation at prior head `d192028ab6cd7f962a7007f0f94c77d6b8b8e4aa` passed 28 tests plus lint/docs/whitespace checks. The branch has since been narrowed to remove the unsupported config placeholder, remove the global artifact Knip ignore, remove Security Matrix dead-code exemptions, clarify docs, and add capability fallback coverage.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Security Matrix runtime-fact evaluation produces deterministic audit decisions from actor, influence source, capability, approval state, and operator policy. The before-tool-call adapter builds the same audit-event shape from explicit boundary facts without emitting, blocking, or mutating execution. Malformed custom policy decisions are ignored instead of being treated as policy output.\n- Runtime boundary addressed: The Security Matrix adapter is now imported from `src/plugins/trusted-tool-policy.ts` through `createTrustedToolPolicySecurityMatrixAuditEvent`, so the model is anchored at the existing trusted before-tool-call policy boundary rather than existing only as allowlisted dead production code.\n- Evidence after fix: The Security Matrix production files were removed from `KNIP_UNUSED_FILE_ALLOWLIST`, and the unsupported `security.matrix.audit.enabled` local config predicate was removed.\n- Observed result after fix: Missing approval facts now remain `approvalState=none` instead of being labeled `not_required`, reducing the risk of misleading future audit records.\n- What was not tested on this latest cleanup head from this session: Runtime hook emission, runtime enforcement, strict config schema adoption, CLI display, plugin UI, and live tool execution are intentionally not changed by this PR.\n",
